</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1398,553,615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">
Based on the mountain name, Danxia, in northern 
<collectingRegion box="[800,940,553,579]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[954,1027,553,579]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">China</collectingCountry>
, and the Latin suffix, 
<emphasis box="[1295,1305,554,579]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">-</emphasis>
ense, of origin, referring to the 
<typeStatus box="[457,508,589,615]" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">type</typeStatus>
locality of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6341220" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6341220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6341220/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="166" startId="4.[189,232,1928,1954]" targetBox="[190,1394,765,1845]" targetPageId="4">
